Dogara disclosed this after laying of the budget proposal during the plenary session. Mustapha Dawaki, chairman, House Committee on Appropriation laid the report. BusinessDay reports that the N8.612 trillion was jerked up by N508 billion. Recall that President Muhammadu had on the 7th November, 2017 laid it before the joint session of the National Assembly. The laying of the budget came six months after the laying of the budget proposal. A breakdown of the budget which was laid before both chambers today (Tuesday) shows that the sum of N530,421,368,624 is for statutory transfer; N2,203,835,365,699 is for debt service; N199 billion is for sinking fund for maturing loans; N3,516,477,902,077 is for recurrent (non debt) expenditure while N2,869,600,351,825 is for development fund for capital expenditure.  KEHINDE AKINTOLA, Abuja